HEADWORD: Semimetallic
<hw>Sem`i*me*tal"lic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to a semimetal; possessing metallic properties in
an inferior degree; resembling metal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

